#! /bin/sh

# Reads multiple dmcrypt-tables from standard input and creates an active
# mapping for every single table. If a mapping already exists, it will be
# skipped, assuming the associated table has already been mapped.
#
# The input may also contain empty lines and line-comments starting with "#"
# which will be completely ignored.
#
# If the 2nd field ("nsecs") of a "crypt" table entry contains a "*"
# immediately (no separating spaces) followed by a count of 512-byte sectors,
# then the 2nd field of the actual table written will be replaced by the count
# of 512-bytes sectors of the device found in the 7th field ("dev") minus the
# count before the "*" minus the count of the 8th field ("startdevsec"). For
# additional comfort, "*0" in the 2nd field can also be written as "*".
#
# The idea of the "*"-feature is that the table does not need to be edited if
# the encrypted volume gets resized. It is assumed that the volume has a
# prefix, then the encrypted data, then a suffix. The size of the prefix is
# specified by the "startdevsec" field, and the size of the suffix is
# specified with the "*" marker in the "nsecs" field.
#
# Every table must be preceded by a line containing the name of the mapping to
# be created for the table following this line. The tables themselves must
# contain one or more lines which will be passed directly to "dmcrypt create".
#
# It is also possible to pass option "-u". In this case, it will be tried to
# unmap all mappings in the reverse order of how the tables are specified.
#
